<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Corroon &amp; Black Corp. said it acquired Collier
Cobb &amp; Associates Inc. in a stock transaction. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   Collier Cobb, a Charlotte, N.C., insurance broker serving
the construction industry, posted revenue of $25.5 million
for 1989 and employs 245 people.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Fitzgerald S. Hudson, chairman and chief executive officer
of Collier Cobb, will serve as chairman of Corroon &amp; Black's
construction industry division, succeeding John R. Lamberson,
president and chief operating officer of Corroon &amp; Black.
