<HL>
   Dutch Consumer Price Index
</HL>
<DATE>
06/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   AMSTERDAM -- The Dutch consumer price index was unchanged
in the month ending in mid-May, but up 2.2% from the
year-earlier period, the Dutch Central Bureau of Statistics
said.
   It was the fourth month in a row that inflation showed a
rise of 2.2% over the year-earlier month. In January, the
price rise was 2.1% from a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   When making its forecast for the Dutch economy earlier in
the year, the Dutch Central Planning Bureau estimated that
inflation for 1990 would amount to 2.1%.
