   Business Brief -- Nissan Motor Co.:
   Japanese Auto Maker Forms
   Finance Subsidiary in U.S.
</HL>
<DATE>
06/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C13
</SO>
<CO>
   NSANY
</CO>
<IN>
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Nissan Motor Co. said it has established a U.S. corporate
finance subsidiary to consolidate finance activities for its
U.S. companies.
   The Japanese auto maker said the new unit, Nissan Capital
of America Inc., will take over the capital markets
activities of Nissan Motor Acceptance Corp., the company's
consumer finance unit. Nissan Capital will begin issuing by
the end of the month $3 billion in U.S. commercial paper that
will be guaranteed by the parent company, Nissan said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Standard &amp; Poor's Corp. and Moody's Investors Service Inc.
assigned Nissan Capital's commercial paper the same rating
currently assigned to Nissan Motor Acceptance's commercial
paper, the company said. S&amp;P's rating is A-1; Moody's rating
is P-1.
</TEXT>
