   Chrysler Financial Corp. -- $300 million of 10.30% notes,
due June 15, 1992, priced at 99.939 to yield 10.33%. The
notes were priced at a spread of 200 basis points above the
Treasury's two-year note. Rated Baa-2 by Moody's Investors
Service Inc. and triple-B-minus by Standard &amp; Poor's Corp.,
the issue will be sold through First Boston Corp. The
Chrysler Financial issue offers bondholder protection in the
form of event-risk language. Investors can put the notes back
to the company at the offering price if the company's debt
ratings falls below investment-grade while Moody's has
Chrysler's debt on its watch list. Earlier this week, Moody's
said it is reviewing the ratings of $22.28 billion of
